OL,5,FDeputy Chief Constable Chris Todd said
OL,6,Fhe wanted to acknowledge the impact
OL,7,Fthe breach had, which was "difficult"
OL,8,Ffor staff and officers.
OL,10,FMr Todd was asked about what the total
OL,11,Fcosts would be, Mr Todd said that a
OL,12,Funiversal payment of up to #500 for
OL,13,Findividual security measures for staff
OL,14,Fand officer had cost #3.4 million.
OL,16,FHe said that around 7,000 claimants
OL,17,Fhad taken legal action against the
OL,18,Forganisation over the breach, which he
OL,19,Fsaid would be "the biggest chunk of
OL,20,Fexpenditure."
